From 13ed9ce047c16f61d6141737dbd969284da90eb4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Guru Pratap Sharma <guruprat@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 22 Aug 2025 07:01:48 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Fix AFC random channel selection

Currently, during random channel selection, there is no check to compare
the EIRP value of SP channels against those of LPI and VLP channels.
This leads to incorrect behavior where, if an SP punctured channel has
lower EIRP than LPI or VLP, the best_power_mode algorithm selects LPI
mode with puncturing, which is invalid.

Additionally, the puncture pattern array does not include the 0x0 pattern,
which represents no puncturing, causing valid channels to be missed.

To fix this, update the selection logic to compare the SP channel EIRP
against LPI and VLP EIRP values, and only include SP channel combinations
in the random channel list if the SP EIRP is higher. If not, skip that
combination and proceed to the next lowest bandwidth.

Also, modify the puncture pattern array to include the 0x0 pattern for
all relevant bandwidths to ensure channels without puncturing are properly
considered.

Fixes: Iefb97147622 (UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL hostapd: Enhance Random Channel
change for AFC)

Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
